Privacy Policy Google Sheets
Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 2/19/2025

Thank you for using our application! Your privacy is important to us, and this Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our Google Sheets integration.

Information We Collect
This application uses Google OAuth 2.0 to access your Google Sheets. As part of this process, we may collect and use the following information:

Your Google account email address (to authenticate access to your Google Sheets).

Access tokens provided by Google to read and write data in your specified spreadsheets.

We do not collect, store, or share your Google account password or any sensitive personal information.

How We Use Your Information
The information collected is used solely for the purpose of interacting with your Google Sheets as requested by you. This may include:

Reading data from your Google Sheets.

Writing or updating data in your Google Sheets.

Creating new spreadsheets (if applicable).

We do not use your data for any other purpose, and we do not share your data with third parties.

Data Security
We take reasonable steps to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. Your Google OAuth tokens are stored securely and are only used to perform the operations you have explicitly authorized.

Third-Party Services
This application relies on Google APIs to access your Google Sheets. Your use of this application is subject to Google's Privacy Policy and terms of service. You can manage your permissions and revoke access at any time through your Google Account settings.

Your Choices
You may revoke the applicationâ€™s access to your Google Sheets at any time by visiting your Google Account permissions page: https://myaccount.google.com/permissions

Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make significant changes, we will notify you either through the app or by other means so you can review the changes.

